## 📌 Architecture of CAI Systems

CAI Systems emerge through structured interactions between humans and AI agents, producing **emergent cognitive regimes**.

### **Figure 2. Structure of CAI Systems**

```mermaid
flowchart TB

    subgraph SYSTEM["CAI SYSTEM (System-Level Intelligence)"]
        SYS["System-Level Intelligence"]
    end

    subgraph REGS["Emergent Cognitive Regimes"]
        R1["Distributed Attention"]
        R2["Collective Anticipation"]
        R3["Emergent Strategy Formation"]
        R4["Hybrid Cognitive Synergy"]
        R5["Collective Intuition"]
        R6["System-Level Identity"]
    end

    subgraph HUM["Human Agents"]
        H1["Human Agent H1"]
        H2["Human Agent H2"]
    end

    subgraph AI["AI Agents"]
        A1["AI Agent A1"]
        A2["AI Agent A2"]
    end

    subgraph INT["Interactions Layer"]
        I1["Communication"]
        I2["Coordination"]
        I3["Feedback Loops"]
    end

    HUM --> INT
    AI --> INT
    INT --> REGS
    REGS --> SYS
```

---

## 📌 CTOR: Experimental Environment

CTOR is a game-based environment with fixed rules where humans and AI agents interact in teams.  
It serves as an **experimental platform** for studying system-level intelligence.

### **Figure 3. CTOR Architecture**

```mermaid
flowchart TB

    subgraph CTOR["CTOR — Shared Game Environment"]
        RULES["Fixed Rules"]
    end

    subgraph HUM["Human Players"]
        H1["H1"]
        H2["H2"]
    end

    subgraph AI["AI Agents"]
        A1["A1"]
        A2["A2"]
    end

    subgraph TEAM["Teams / Matches"]
        T1["1v1 / 2v2 / Hybrid Teams"]
    end

    subgraph TRAJ["Game Trajectories"]
        TR["Actions, States, Timing"]
    end

    HUM --> TEAM
    AI --> TEAM
    TEAM --> TRAJ
    TRAJ --> CTOR
```

